1. generate package.json
    (npm init -y)

2. create express appli (--> http server + other stuff) and call the server

3. install mongoose and connect to mongodb server

  rest api-- mongodb(database) native driver-->db server
  rest api-- mongoose(tool to connect to db) odm(obj doc mapping) tool-->db server

     [127.0.0.1 works in the place of localhost. its the ip address of it] 


4. build user rest api
       -create user
       -read all users
       -read a user by id
       -update a user by id
       -delete a user by id

5. create schema and model of the resource[user]

6. create user api and define routes